annotationA: Delta-1-Pyrroline-5-carboxylate dehydrogenase 1 is a conserved, nuclear-encoded mitochondrial matrix enzyme. It is a member of the aldehyde dehydrogenase superfamily involved in proline degradation
annotationB: Glutamate dehydrogenase [NAD(P)+] activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: oxidation-reduction process; glutamate catabolic process to 2-oxoglutarate; Belongs to the Glu/Leu/Phe/Val dehydrogenases family
